<TITLE> BIMSTEC meeting starts Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 07 (bdnews24.com)The senior officials' meeting of a BIMSTEC ministerial conference on poverty alleviation starts in Dhaka Tuesday. Ministers from Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, Myanmar, Nepal, Sri Lanka and Thailand will meet Wednesday to find ways of expediting poverty alleviation in the BIMSTEC countries. Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed will inaugurate the ministerial meeting at Dhaka Sonargaon Hotel. Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam will preside over the opening function. The senior officials of the member countries will discuss different aspects of poverty alleviation and prepare the agenda for the ministerial meeting, slated for Wednesday. According to the agenda of the senior officials' meeting, the member countries will exchange their experiences on poverty alleviation. The agenda will also include agriculture, health, education, and small and medium enterprises, aiming at achieving millennium development goals in the member countries. Bay of Bengal Initiative for Multi-Sectoral Technical and Economic Cooperation (BIMSTEC) was formed on June 6, 1997 in Bangkok, the capital of Thailand. The seven countries have endorsed a plan for a free trade pact to be signed by 2017 while the three most advanced countries of the region (India, Sri Lanka, and Thailand) have committed to liberalising trade by 2012. bdn
